rComments: I needed to take this class to fulfill one of my requirements.  I had no interest in it whatsoever.  But the prof made it a somewhat interesting class.  She clearly knows what she is talking about and makes it a point to repeat concepts.  She initially had a hard time projecting her voice but it got better.  She was fair and approachable.
Probably the worst professor i've had yet. she spoke quietly, was clearly uncomfortable and only seemed enthusiastic when we were studying the opium war.

Professor Wright was very difficult to hear during lectures as she appeared very nervous nearly every lecture, however she is very knowledgeable and clear when you can hear her. Overall Professor Wright lacks presentation skills during lecture. If you need a interesting or charismatic prof to enjoy and succeed  I would avoid this class.
Very thorough and knowledgeable.  She is not the most charismatic lecturer but she is very clear and approachable.  Did not enjoy my first lecture and she became my favourite prof.
Really helpful. She is young but known what she is talking about.

Not a good lecturer. Seems uncomfortable in public speaking. Not enthusiastic, dynamic or engaging. I liked most of the course content (10 Days That Shook the World), so I did not drop. But if you need a good Prof. to enjoy history, beware of taking a course with her. She did get a little better as the year went on, but not significantly.
